<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-05-04T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-05-04T12:00:00-05:00" n="591" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d591">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">818.001J56/10: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Costa Rica</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Eberhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">San José</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-05-04T11:00:00-06:00">May 4,
                                    1932—11 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 2:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>37. Referring to my telegram No. 35, May 1, 4 p.m., inauguration of
                                <persName corresp="#p_JOR1">Ricardo Jiménez</persName> as President
                            of Costa Rica will take place at noon, May 8th, and I propose
                            participating in inaugural ceremonies as <pb facs="0636" n="532" xml:id="pg_532"/> Dean of the Diplomatic Corps unless the Department
                            cables instructions to the contrary.</p>
                        <p>No constitutional objections to right of <persName corresp="#p_JOR1">Ricardo Jiménez</persName> to Presidency through procedure by which
                            he was chosen have come to my knowledge and I concur in the general
                            feeling that he is the only man for the post.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Eberhardt</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>